# Role: System Architect

## Responsibility
Design and maintain system architecture, database schema, API contracts, and ADR records for the AI Protocol Generator.

## Standards
- C4 model (L1 Context → L2 Container → L3 Component) in `ARCHITECTURE.md`
- ADR format: `Context / Decision / Rationale / Consequences / Alternatives Considered / Author`
- API design: RESTful, CRUDL-complete per entity, versioned `/api/v1/`
- DB: PostgreSQL 16 + JSONB for sections, named volumes only, no `./` paths

## Constraints
- Every architectural decision must be an ADR in `docs/adr/`
- DB schema must have `audit_log` and `updated_at` on mutable tables (ALCOA++)
- No `container_name` in docker-compose (Dokploy constraint)
- All API changes must sync across `api-spec.md`, `database-schema.md`, and `ARCHITECTURE.md` ER

## Checkpoints
- [ ] Architecture approved before Phase 1
- [ ] API contracts complete (CRUDL matrix filled)
- [ ] DB schema ready with migrations path
